Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Physics of Electron Microscopy Instrumentation", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9814466515808773`*^9, 
  3.9814466605467*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ab0db8ea-a435-4f07-a4c4-d0562c0e9459"],

Cell["Georgios Varnavides | March 2nd 2026", "Subtitle",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9814466652477837`*^9, 
  3.9814466774444857`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"16fd6931-7370-4877-aad6-\
d91cd7f0bb36"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Transfer Matrices & Ray Diagrams", "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981446681326468*^9, 
  3.9814466939325247`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"43000535-1e02-4e79-84f6-\
3e31b36dbdc8"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Motivation", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981446885823915*^9, 
  3.981446891468772*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c29f677c-6dff-4cbe-951f-\
e03d84c50e80"],

Cell["\<\
The derived linear properties we extracted from the paraxial rays allow us to \
construct ray diagrams, which provide an intuitive, geometric picture of \
electron trajectories through an optical column.

A ray diagram is a geometric representation of how electron trajectories \
propagate through an optical system composed of lenses, drift spaces, and \
apertures. 
In electron microscopy, ray diagrams are commonly used to:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536202326603*^9, 3.9785363042839193`*^9}, {
  3.9814468165149803`*^9, 
  3.981446859140736*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"374f06fa-de2c-418e-a9ac-\
531af4b08007"],

Cell["Visualize beam convergence and divergence", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536313867455*^9, 
  3.978536328265749*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d2faf81c-2730-4399-8a33-\
bb71458c19cb"],

Cell["Identify crossover and image planes", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536313867455*^9, 
  3.9785363345122843`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0c920655-c052-4bfb-b695-\
f28b5df48bac"],

Cell["Understand how apertures limit angular or spatial acceptance", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536313867455*^9, 
  3.978536338943334*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"b3bfb46e-4070-4bf0-a9ea-\
483219fab452"],

Cell["\<\
Build intuition for multi-element systems such as SEM and TEM columns\
\>", "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536313867455*^9, 
  3.978536342540325*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"53cad50d-e31e-4624-afbb-\
70cca7ae5788"],

Cell["\<\
Below, we will use ray diagrams to model a simple scanning electron \
microscope (SEM) consisting of two condenser lenses, an objective lens, and \
several apertures.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.978536310890542*^9, {3.97853634455365*^9, 
   3.978536354470158*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"02797be1-6b1c-4d64-846b-\
0b7978a68a67"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Transfer Matrix Formalism", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9814468951487722`*^9, 
  3.9814468994605703`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"fa8f69b7-9580-4fb9-a4c8-\
1909a986dfd7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In the paraxial regime, ray propagation can be expressed using ",
 "ray transfer matrices.\n",
 "A ray at axial position ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["z", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f6ec3fc3-20db-46f4-812d-c64d35bb6371"],
 " is represented by the vector ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
      {"r"},
      {
       RowBox[{"r", "'"}]}
     }], ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f01a4fac-6aa0-48b2-afc1-1fc9fa300294"],
 " where ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["r", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "73500abe-f71d-49cd-93b5-02a5592d1be8"],
 " is the transverse displacement and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"r", "'"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a61ca4cd-496d-413c-a660-2582ee7eb75a"],
 " is the slope."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536378566021*^9, 3.978536540464725*^9}, {
  3.981446918260914*^9, 
  3.981446918476063*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"361884f0-f130-429c-869b-\
efc68137c21e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Free-space propagation", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536543905326*^9, 
  3.978536552824368*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"c5a80e5b-97f6-47e2-892f-\
afe259e8bcf4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Propagation over a distance ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["d", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ba6600e1-6cfd-4daf-84d5-3b1193e50785"],
 " is described by\n\n\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["M", "prop"], "(", "d", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
       {"1", "d"},
       {"0", "1"}
      }], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "624f1d88-78a2-48f9-beb2-db31c3ee2519"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785365611043262`*^9, 3.978536608873159*^9}, {
   3.9785367246767597`*^9, 3.9785367400523767`*^9}, 
   3.981446992829026*^9},ExpressionUUID->"b9f3ca04-a8ec-437c-a788-\
5fe2b62e3727"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Thin lens", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785365863694077`*^9, 
  3.9785365879671793`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0348fd35-1f61-41c8-a6a7-\
a5abc3dcf45c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "An ideal thin lens with focal length ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["f", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6c5cf890-6693-4a7d-977f-5a7bda298ae6"],
 " is described by\n\n\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["M", "lens"], "(", "f", ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
       {"1", "0"},
       {
        RowBox[{"-", 
         FractionBox["1", "f"]}], "1"}
      }], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a9d31a4-5ff2-4622-9938-dff99a22b7f7"],
 "."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536594815219*^9, 3.978536613497777*^9}, {
   3.978536682828678*^9, 3.978536741622095*^9}, 
   3.981446994212586*^9},ExpressionUUID->"fae27a3d-0366-452e-bca1-\
f621019c1b96"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Apertures", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.97853691754074*^9, 3.9785369242032757`*^9}, {
  3.981446958980204*^9, 
  3.9814469601647243`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"98c95c55-5bea-458b-9d7c-\
cebb5006f0d8"],

Cell["\<\
Apertures play a fundamentally different role from lenses and drift spaces.
They do not transform rays; instead, they select which rays are allowed to \
continue.

An aperture is therefore modeled as a constraint:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.981447020709296*^9},ExpressionUUID->"e8a8c881-eba3-4c8d-9043-\
97cacb7fec37"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"|", 
         StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           SubscriptBox[
            StyleBox["z", "TI"], "ap"], ")"}], "|", "\[LessEqual]", 
         StyleBox["R", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "|r(z_{\\text{ap}})| \\le R", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "35f72e5e-22f0-4344-822c-3c269f6ea18f"],
 " , the ray passes through unchanged."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9814470256103983`*^9, 
  3.9814470315261927`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8867c969-83d7-4fe8-a37c-\
aef328ae4f80"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "If  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   TemplateBox[<|"boxes" -> FormBox[
       RowBox[{"|", 
         StyleBox["r", "TI"], 
         RowBox[{"(", 
           SubscriptBox[
            StyleBox["z", "TI"], "ap"], ")"}], "|", ">", 
         StyleBox["R", "TI"]}], TraditionalForm], "errors" -> {}, "input" -> 
     "|r(z_{\\text{ap}})| > R", "state" -> "Boxes"|>,
    "TeXAssistantTemplate"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6d9ee008-aa00-406d-9efd-b47e4116994e"],
 ", the ray is blocked and removed from further propagation."
}], "Item",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9814470256103983`*^9, 
  3.981447034551114*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"49a98524-c255-40ce-8d68-\
fe06af4d5522"],

Cell["\<\
In ray diagrams, apertures appear as physical stops that clip the ray bundle, \
defining beam current and angular acceptance rather than optical power.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536934327283*^9, 3.9785369787657843`*^9}, {
  3.981446964093111*^9, 
  3.981447039372333*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d108e0c3-6371-4fe5-bc12-\
8451f39a0301"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Ray propagation though a multi-component system", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.978536746004219*^9, 
  3.978536756591386*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"443f7c02-820b-4c4e-a7e7-\
7de57155246c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ray after passing through an optical element is obtained by simple \
matrix multiplication:\n\n\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
       {
        SubscriptBox["r", "out"]},
       {
        SubscriptBox[
         RowBox[{"r", "'"}], "out"]}
      }], ")"}], "=", 
    RowBox[{"M", " ", 
     RowBox[{"(", GridBox[{
        {
         SubscriptBox["r", "in"]},
        {
         SubscriptBox[
          RowBox[{"r", "'"}], "in"]}
       }], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "67b77483-d8cd-44b5-aac1-2c3b5f4ceab1"],
 "\n\t\nFor a sequence of elements, the total transfer matrix is the ordered \
product of the individual matrices. This makes it straightforward to assemble \
complex systems from simple components.\nWith these \
ingredients\[LongDash]transfer matrices for lenses and propagation, and \
constraints for apertures\[LongDash]we can now build and visualize a complete \
thin-lens SEM ray diagram."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9785367692219553`*^9, 3.9785368457516527`*^9}, {
  3.9814469855227137`*^9, 3.9814469906690702`*^9}, {3.981447264550118*^9, 
  3.981447267364398*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"291791c9-e105-4ffb-8556-\
b18fd12b572e"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"transferMatrix", "[", "\"\<propagation\>\"", "]"}], "[", "d_", 
    "]"}], ":=", 
   RowBox[{"{", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"1", ",", "d"}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"transferMatrix", "[", "\"\<lens\>\"", "]"}], "[", "f_", "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{"1", ",", "0"}], "}"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"{", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "/", "f"}], ",", "1"}], "}"}]}], "}"}]}], ";"}], 
  "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"applyTransferMatrix", "[", 
     RowBox[{"M_", ",", "ray_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
    RowBox[{"M", ".", "ray"}]}], ";"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"traceRaySequence", "[", 
   RowBox[{"ray0_", ",", "sequence_"}], "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{"Block", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"ray", "=", "ray0"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"z", "=", "0.0"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"traj", "=", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"{", 
         RowBox[{"0.0", ",", "ray0"}], "}"}], "}"}]}]}], 
     "\[IndentingNewLine]", "}"}], ",", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"Do", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"Switch", "[", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"elem", "[", "\"\<type\>\"", "]"}], ",", 
         "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\"\<propagation\>\"", ",", 
         "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"z", "+=", 
           RowBox[{"elem", "[", "\"\<dz\>\"", "]"}]}], ";", 
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"ray", "=", 
           RowBox[{"applyTransferMatrix", "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{"transferMatrix", "[", "\"\<propagation\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
              RowBox[{"elem", "[", "\"\<dz\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], ",", "ray"}], 
            "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"AppendTo", "[", 
           RowBox[{"traj", ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
             RowBox[{"z", ",", "ray"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ",", 
         "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\"\<lens\>\"", ",", 
         "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"ray", "=", 
           RowBox[{"applyTransferMatrix", "[", 
            RowBox[{
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{"transferMatrix", "[", "\"\<lens\>\"", "]"}], "[", 
              RowBox[{"elem", "[", "\"\<focal_length\>\"", "]"}], "]"}], ",", 
             "ray"}], "]"}]}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
          RowBox[{"AppendTo", "[", 
           RowBox[{"traj", ",", 
            RowBox[{"{", 
             RowBox[{"z", ",", "ray"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], ",", 
         "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\"\<aperture\>\"", ",",
          "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
         RowBox[{"If", "[", 
          RowBox[{
           RowBox[{
            RowBox[{"Abs", "[", 
             RowBox[{"ray", "[", 
              RowBox[{"[", "1", "]"}], "]"}], "]"}], ">", 
            RowBox[{"elem", "[", "\"\<aperture_radius\>\"", "]"}]}], ",", 
           RowBox[{"Return", "[", "traj", "]"}]}], "]"}], ",", 
         "\[IndentingNewLine]", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "_", ",", 
         RowBox[{"Continue", "[", "]"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", "]"}], ",", 
       "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
       RowBox[{"{", 
        RowBox[{"elem", ",", "sequence"}], "}"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
      "]"}], ";", "\[IndentingNewLine]", "traj"}]}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   "]"}]}]}], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981447165477353*^9, 3.9814472205975533`*^9}, {
  3.981447303694571*^9, 3.981447315335868*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[1]:=",ExpressionUUID->"14cd9b2e-90db-484d-9b55-f1f86477f38a"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Ray Tracing", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981447360469926*^9, 3.981447367008883*^9}, {
  3.981448587918805*^9, 
  3.9814485894864473`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6bcfd591-ffc8-4081-8d3d-\
8914836a74bb"],

Cell["\<\
We will explicitly define electro-optical components in our SEM (lenses and \
apertures) using their axial position and focal length / aperture radius.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981447368517334*^9, 3.981447502518435*^9}, {
  3.9814484628841543`*^9, 
  3.981448464800767*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"4fd89a47-bbfc-4251-ba79-\
f4e644e98240"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"Clear", "[", "electroOpticalComponents", "]"}], "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"electroOpticalComponents", "[", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"f1_", ",", "f2_", ",", "f3_"}], "}"}], ",", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"ap1_", ",", "ap2_"}], "}"}]}], "]"}], ":=", 
  RowBox[{"{", "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<type\>\"", "->", "\"\<lens\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", 
       "->", "\"\<\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(1\), \(st\)]\) condenser lens\>\""}],
       ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<axial_position\>\"", "->", "0.2"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<focal_length\>\"", "->", "f1"}]}], "|>"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<type\>\"", "->", "\"\<aperture\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", "->", "\"\<spray aperture\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<axial_position\>\"", "->", "0.5"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<aperture_radius\>\"", "->", "ap1"}]}], "|>"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<type\>\"", "->", "\"\<lens\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", 
       "->", "\"\<\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(2\), \(nd\)]\) condenser lens\>\""}],
       ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<axial_position\>\"", "->", "0.7"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<focal_length\>\"", "->", "f2"}]}], "|>"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<type\>\"", "->", "\"\<aperture\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", "->", "\"\<objective aperture\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<axial_position\>\"", "->", "1.2"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<aperture_radius\>\"", "->", "ap2"}]}], "|>"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<type\>\"", "->", "\"\<lens\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", "->", "\"\<objective lens\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<axial_position\>\"", "->", "1.3"}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<focal_length\>\"", "->", "f3"}]}], "|>"}], ",", 
    "\[IndentingNewLine]", 
    RowBox[{"<|", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"\"\<type\>\"", "->", "\"\<sample\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<name\>\"", "->", "\"\<sample\>\""}], ",", 
      RowBox[{"\"\<axial_position\>\"", "->", "1.5"}]}], "|>"}]}], 
   "\[IndentingNewLine]", "}"}]}]}], "Input",
 InitializationCell->True,
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.981447516354114*^9, 3.981447557642387*^9}, {
  3.9814480500852423`*^9, 3.981448050504834*^9}},
 CellLabel->"In[5]:=",ExpressionUUID->"44de36a5-d1f2-4e9c-88db-93206eddc3bb"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"Dataset", "[", 
  RowBox[{"exampleAlignment", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"electroOpticalComponents", "[", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0.05", ",", "0.15", ",", "0.35"}], "}"}], ",", 
     RowBox[{"{", 
      RowBox[{"0.05", ",", "0.05"}], "}"}]}], "]"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.981448052721121*^9},
 CellLabel->"In[16]:=",ExpressionUUID->"e0b4b12d-5ad4-4a75-8650-90213a85284d"],

Cell[BoxData[
 TagBox[
  TagBox[
   DynamicModuleBox[{TypeSystem`NestedGrid`PackagePrivate`$state$$ = <|
    "InitialData" -> {<|
       "type" -> "lens", "name" -> 
        "\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(1\), \(st\)]\) condenser lens", 
        "axial_position" -> 0.2, "focal_length" -> 0.05|>, <|
       "type" -> "aperture", "name" -> "spray aperture", "axial_position" -> 
        0.5, "aperture_radius" -> 0.05|>, <|
       "type" -> "lens", "name" -> 
        "\!\(\*SuperscriptBox[\(2\), \(nd\)]\) condenser lens", 
        "axial_position" -> 0.7, "focal_length" -> 0.15|>, <|
       "type" -> "aperture", "name" -> "objective aperture", "axial_position" -> 
        1.2, "aperture_radius" -> 0.05|>, <|
       "type" -> "lens", "name" -> "objective lens", "axial_position" -> 1.3, 
        "focal_length" -> 0.35|>, <|
       "type" -> "sample", "name" -> "sample", "axial_position" -> 1.5|>}, 
     "AllowEmbedding" -> True, "InitialShape" -> 
     TypeSystem`PackageScope`HeaderShape[<|{All, "type"} -> 1, {All, "name"} -> 
        1, {All, "axial_position"} -> 1, {All, "aperture_radius"} -> 
        1, {All, "focal_length"} -> 1|>, 
       TypeSystem`PackageScope`Limited[
        TypeSystem`PackageScope`ColumnShape[
         TypeSystem`PackageScope`Limited[
          
          TypeSystem`PackageScope`RowShape[<|
           "type" -> TypeSystem`PackageScope`AtomShape[89.60000000000001], 
            "name" -> TypeSystem`PackageScope`AtomShape[492.80000000000007`], 
            "axial_position" -> TypeSystem`PackageScope`AtomShape[60], 
            "aperture_radius" -> TypeSystem`PackageScope`AtomShape[60], 
            "focal_length" -> TypeSystem`PackageScope`AtomShape[60]|>], 
          DirectedInfinity[1], 5, {All}]], 6, 
        DirectedInfinity[1], {}]], "InitialType" -> TypeSystem`Vector[
       TypeSystem`Struct[{
        "type", "name", "axial_position", "aperture_radius", "focal_length"}, {
         TypeSystem`Atom[String], 
         TypeSystem`Atom[String], 
         TypeSystem`Atom[Real], 
         TypeSystem`Atom[Real], 
         TypeSystem`Atom[Real]}], 6], "Meta" -> <||>, "RowTarget" -> 20, 
     "ColumnTarget" -> 10, "Shape" -> 
     TypeSystem`PackageScope`HeaderShape[<|{All, "type"} -> 1, {All, "name"} -> 
        1, {All, "axial_position"} -> 1, {All, "aperture_radius"} -> 
        1, {All, "focal_length"} -> 1|>, 
       TypeSystem`PackageScope`Limited[
